The '''Mission to Rattatak''' was an opportunity for [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] to seek a new ally with the power to defeat the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]].

==The mission==
[[File:Dooku_Ventress_duel.png|thumb|left|250px|Dooku taunts Ventress as they cross blades]]
In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], on the planet [[Rattatak/Legends|Rattatak]], at a combat ring called [[the Cauldron]], Dooku went to the Cauldron in an attempt to find an assassin for the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|CIS]]. There he encountered a mysterious fighter who dominated every opponent in the combat ring with the skilled use of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and her lightsabers. She introduced herself to him as [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]], a [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] warrior. After denouncing her claims to be a Sith, Dooku challenged Asajj in combat and defeated her. Dooku denied that she was a Sith, pointing out she had fear, a feature he claimed Sith do not have. Ventress tried to kill Dooku, enraged at this comment, but Dooku used [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]] to knock her unconscious.

Ventress awoke after a long sleep. She found her lightsabers on a table. Dooku came at her surprisingly, forcing Ventress into a duel. Ventress [[Force jump/Legends|Force Jumped]] and [[Telekinesis/Legends|grabbed]] her [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]]. The duel began. They both dueled with all their anger at each other. Dooku taunted Ventress by saying that if she was a Sith, she would have defeated him quickly. This enraged Ventress, and caused her to become reckless in her attack. Dooku finally [[Telekinesis/Legends#Force pull|pulled]] her lightsabers and [[Sun djem/Legends|chopped them in half]], winning the duel.

==Aftermath==
Dooku was so impressed with her skills that he presented her to [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]], who was watching via [[Hologram/Legends|hologram]], and gave Ventress an important assignment&mdash;assassinate [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]]. Ventress, after receiving [[Komari Vosa]]'s lightsabers, left in a [[Ginivex-class starfighter/Legends|Fanblade starfighter]] to kill him.

